RelatedSentence: A group of pensioners is claiming victory now that their Housing New Zealand homes will not be fast - tracked for redevelopment .
A 42 - unit apartment complex in Freemans Bay , Auckland , was put out for expressions of interest from developers last year by Housing New Zealand .
But the area has not been earmarked as a special housing area under Auckland Council 's housing accord , which means fast - track redevelopment will not go ahead .
A retiree who 's lived in the complex , Bob Tait , says the process has put many of the residents under stress .
